  "prompt": "What is the meaning of tax rebate? As per the year budget, tax rebate is now 5000 for salary more than 5 lakh. What does it mean in a lay man language?",
  "response": "In simple terms, a tax rebate is a refund or relief on taxes that you can claim, which effectively reduces the amount of tax you owe. \n\nRegarding the specific information you provided: If someone earns more than 5 lakh (500,000) rupees per year, they are now eligible to receive a tax rebate of 5,000 rupees. This means that when calculating the amount of tax they owe, they can subtract 5,000 rupees from their total tax bill, effectively reducing the amount payable by 5,000 rupees. \n\nFor example, if your total tax liability was calculated to be 20,000 rupees, with the tax rebate applied, you would only need to pay 15,000 rupees (because 20,000 minus 5,000 equals 15,000).",
